    Level-1 Main Claim: {"claim": "The premise of the motion is scientifically flawed because plants are sentient beings, and life inherently requires death.", "argument": ["Plants are sentient beings with complex communication systems.", "Claiming plants lack faces is an arbitrary distinction.", "Life inherently requires death.", "Animals play a crucial role in ecological health.", "Ethically raised livestock offers nutritional and environmental benefits.", "Proper animal management can combat climate change and desertification.", "Claiming plants don't experience harm relies on a narrow definition of suffering.", "Plant responses to stimuli demonstrate a complex biological reality."]}
